Beef ho (chow) fun ðð¥¢

My favourite weeknight dinner!

For the beef:
* 400-500g skirt/flank beef steak, trimmed
* 1 tsp light soy sauce
* 1 tsp dark soy sauce
* 1 teaspoon cornstarch
* 1 tsp bicarb soda
* 1 tsp sugar
* 1 Tbsp high-fry oil
Â 
For the stir fry:
* 2 Tbsp high-fry oil
* 200g beansprouts
* 1 bunch spring onions, chopped roughly
* 3 cloves garlic, chopped
* (Optional) 1 bunch tender-stem Broccoli (broccolini)
Then:
* 400-500g flat rice noodles

For the sauce:
* 1 Tbsp dark soy sauce
* 1 Tbsp light soy sauce
* 2 Tbsp oyster sauce
* 1 Tbsp sesame oil
* 1 tsp sugar
* 1 lemon juice

Method:
1. Cut thin slices of beef
2. Coat beef slices in ingredients and set aside for 10 minutes (or ideally 30 if you have time!)
3. Cut all your other ingredients to size
4. If you have dried rice noodles, cook them per packet instructions and rinse once cooked
5. Fry in a wok or a large fry pan on high heat the beef with a bit of high-fry oil
6. Set aside beef once browned
7. Add all other stir fry ingredients and cook for 2 minutes 
8. Add the noodles
9. Add all sauces to a bowl and then into the stir fry and coat the noodles until brown colour 
10. Add the beef back in and cook for 2 minutes
11. Serve hot & fresh

5 tips for perfect scallops â¬ï¸

Sign up for my newsletter to keep up to date with recipes and cooking techniques! Comment âNEWSLETTERâ and Iâll send you a link to your DMs to join my community!

5 steps:

1. Pick larger scallops at the store - larger has more surface area for a better sear and also less likely to overcook

2. Thoroughly pat dry after seasoning and before searing. If there is any moisture it will stick to the pan and wonât get a good sear.

3. Do the mercury ball water test to make sure your stainless steel pan is hot enough. If water dances on top of the surface, it is hot enough to add oil and will essentially be nonstick.

4. Sear on medium high heat on the first side until there is a good crust.

5. Cook on low heat on the second side and baste with butter or fat. If you cook on higher heat it will overcook!

In this video with LPGA Tour player Jessica Korda,
youâll see a move that most amateurs overlook:
Both the club and the hands drop down together.

Some players only drop the club â and end up flipping at impact.
Others drop just the hands â and still come over the top.
But when hands and club fall together, naturally and on plane,
thatâs when the magic happens.

The key?
Itâs not about forcing it.
Itâs about teaching your body to feel the right motion â
over and over, until it becomes automatic.

Start slow.
Stand in front of a mirror.
Keep your hips and shoulders in the backswing position â
and just let your arms and hands drop down.

It might feel exaggerated at first â
but thatâs exactly how your brain starts to build a new pattern.

And when the pattern sticks,
youâll stop flipping, stay on plane, and strike the ball cleaner than ever.

Do it slow. Do it often.
And let your swing remember whatâs right.

click the link in my bio or in the description below

Color Pattern: 
Calico cats have a distinctive coat with three colours: white, black, and orange. The distribution and intensity of these colours can vary widely.
 
Mostly Females: 
The majority of calico cats are female. This is due to the genetics of the colour pattern, which is linked to the X chromosome. Male calico cats are rare and often sterile.

Genetic Mutation: 
The colour pattern results from a genetic mutation related to the X chromosomes. Since females have two X chromosomes, they are more likely to exhibit the calico pattern.

Breeds: 
The calico colour pattern can occur in many cat breeds, including the American Shorthair, Persian, and Maine Coon, among others.

Good Luck Symbols: 
Calico cats are considered good luck in some cultures. For example, in Japan, they are known as âManeki-Nekoâ or âbeckoning cats,â which are believed to bring good fortune to their owners.

State Cat: 
The calico cat is designated as the official state cat of Maryland in the United States. This honours the stateâs traditional colours: black, orange, and white.

Personality: 
Calico cats can have diverse personalities due to their pattern appearing in various breeds. They are often regarded as independent, affectionate, and sometimes aggressive.

Rare Albino Calicos: 
While extremely rare, albino calico cats can exist. These cats display a diluted version of the calico coloration that appears fainter and less vibrant.

As we strapped into our snowboards and rode a heel edge track out CPR ridge I could see people migrate to the gondola windows as the cabs zipped by, likely wondering what a little 7 year old girl in a tutu was doing navigating the precarious ridge between the black diamond terrain that fell East into the morning light and the double black diamond terrain that fell West.

This is about celebrating the small moments and steps that eventually lead up to a completed picture and yes thereâs even fun to be found in these sometimes daunting processes because if youâre not enjoying it and laughing at the end then why are you even doing it?

People wonder where she gets her âI can do anythingâ mentality and it continues to be bolstered in moments like this where her fear and caution are rightfully validated but not given complete control and with some support sheâs able to step just beyond what she previously thought possible.
